default1.3default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe demand for heat is reducing as buildings and installations are being built or refurbished to higher stan
defaultdards.  The Building Regulations are regularly up-dated to bring the standards of building fabric and internal systems to a greater efficiency, thereby reducing energy requirements.
default1.4default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIt is important that there is an incentive to ensure that existing buildin
defaultg owners and operators do not take the easy route and decide not to refurbish the building and accept that energy usage and running costs are high.  The capital required to carry out the refurbishment is not always easy to obtain and this is a factor in de
defaultcisions made not to improve the structure.
default2default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultHeat Generationdefault2.1default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe industrial/commercial sector uses large amounts of energy, mainly gas and oil to generate the forms of heat required for the various types of use. Some of these processes are using very old equ
defaultipment in out of date applications. The costs of up-dating an industrial process can in some situations warrant the move to another part of the world, thereby causing a loss of UK jobs and a deficit in the balance of payments.
default2.2default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe variations in the types 
defaultand grade of heat required in the industrial/commercial sector are extensive and this gives rise to great difficulty in using the renewable technologies.
default There are processes which will use a constant volume of hot water which could be ideal for a biomass b
defaultoiler, CHP or heat pump which work more efficiently at a constant load, however, the temperature specified can also play a part in determining whether these renewable technologies will operate in the most efficient way.
default2.3default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe DECC Heat Strategy is a good bas
defaultis for changing the industry perception to the way that heat is generated, however, the design concepts in the industrial/commercial sector are so varied that the basis of reducing fossil fuels usage to such a low percentage of heat generated will be extre
defaultmely difficult to achieve.
default2.4default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe industrial/commercial industry accepts that renewable fuels will play a major part in reducing energy usage and GHG emissions. Manufacturers in this sector are developing products to maximise the use of renewable fuels. Howev
defaulter, the technologies such as biomass, CHP and heat pumps, operate at their most efficient when they are delivering a steady heat load. Solar thermal products have a very intermittent supply of heat due to the vagaries of the 
defaultBritish weather.  The working t
defaultemperatures of each technology are different and trying to work outside those parameters tends to reduce efficiency.  The most energy efficient way to generate heat is to combine one or two renewable energy fuelled pieces of equipment working with a gas or
default oil boiler to give the top up when the demand increases. The addition of intelligent pumps and 
defaultcontrols
default will ensure that the renewable fuelled equipment will operate at a constant demand and the boilers will take the peak and instantaneous heat demands.
default2.5default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultH
defaulteat generation in industrial/commercial installations tends to vary over a very wide range dependent on usage and time of year and therefore the use of renewable technology to supply the base load with fossil 
defaultfuelled
default appliances acting in support will give 
defaultthe most fuel efficient operation with reduced GHG emission.
default default2.6default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
